This paper focuses on the representation of unordered, variable-sized inputs using neural networks, which is a common problem in machine learning and natural language processing. The paper proposes a new approach using complex-weighted multiset automata, which is relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper extends the DeepSets model, which is a neural network architecture for set-oriented learning, making it relevant to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper also discusses the theoretical justification for the Transformer model's use of sinusoidal functions, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
